descript.abstract: U.S. ZIP Code Areas (Three-Digit) represents the first three digits of a ZIP Code. The first digit of a five-digit ZIP Code divides the United States into 10 large groups of states numbered from 0 in the Northeast to 9 in the far West. Within these areas, each state is divided into an average of 10 smaller geographic areas, identified by the second and third digits. These digits, in conjunction with the first digit, represent a sectional center facility or a mail processing facility area. These areas are serviced by the U.S. Post Office Sectional Center Facility (SCF). Note that a single SCF often services multiple three-digit areas.
descript.purpose: U.S. ZIP Code Areas (Three-Digit) provides area and population for each three-digit ZIP Code area in the United States.
descript.supplinf: Largest scale when displaying the data: 1:50,000.

procstep.procdesc: The following steps were performed by Esri: Copied U.S. ZIP Code Areas (Five-Digit) and renamed it. Added the ZIP3 field and dissolved on the first three digits in the ZIP Code. Summarized the STATE and SQMI fields. For ZIP3 values of "000" and "001", calculated STATE = "US" (federal lands). Summarized the POP2012 field ignoring any "-99" records. Recalculated the POP12_SQMI field. Removed and reordered fields. Converted the data set to SDC. Created ArcGIS® layer file (.lyr), projection file (.prj), and spatial indices.
procstep.srcused: TomTom MultiNet Postal Districts and Administrative Areas v. 2012.12

horizpa.horizpar: Horizontal positional accuracy is dependent on geographic area. In most areas, accuracy is between 5 and 25 meters (16 and 82 feet). In some areas, accuracy is off by up to several tens of meters (100 feet or more). In the poorest areas, accuracy is off by up to 100 meters (328 feet).

dataqual.logic: The shapefile is converted to SDC (Smart Data Compression) format using tools in ArcGIS. The SDC data set is then imported into a file geodatabase to verify, validate, and if needed repair the geometry.
dataqual.complete: After processing, the data set is checked for drawing display and number of records and file sizes compared with source materials.
